{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"o5p95ZOzuszn4wAUYarUr","title":"8 Forecasting","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[],"anchors":{"forecasting":{"type":"header","text":"Forecasting","value":"forecasting","line":8,"column":0},"missing-data":{"type":"header","text":"Missing Data","value":"missing-data","line":21,"column":0},"omitted-variables-are-uncorrelated-with-factors":{"type":"header","text":"Omitted variables are uncorrelated with factors","value":"omitted-variables-are-uncorrelated-with-factors","line":25,"column":0},"omitted-variables-are-correlated-with-factors":{"type":"header","text":"Omitted variables are correlated with factors","value":"omitted-variables-are-correlated-with-factors","line":29,"column":0},"pca-regression-approach":{"type":"header","text":"PCA Regression Approach","value":"pca-regression-approach","line":33,"column":0},"genrealized-and-dynamic-pca-regression-approach":{"type":"header","text":"Genrealized and Dynamic PCA Regression Approach","value":"genrealized-and-dynamic-pca-regression-approach","line":35,"column":0},"state-space-approach":{"type":"header","text":"State Space Approach","value":"state-space-approach","line":37,"column":0},"mixed-frequencies-nowcaastingbackcasting":{"type":"header","text":"Mixed Frequencies (Nowcaasting/Backcasting)","value":"mixed-frequencies-nowcaastingbackcasting","line":39,"column":0}},"fname":"LSE.8","updated":1636096567801,"created":1635129375865,"parent":"qDVp6IFHf6FiUdSgxwZMA","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"5ef94a18291489474383314f3b962a72","custom":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"forecasting\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#forecasting\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Forecasting</h1>\n<p>This section deals with how factor models are used in the context of applied forecasting, and more specifically, how to forecast any <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_{it}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> series within the panel used to construct the factors themselves. I.e. this is not simply a factor augmented forecast exercise.</p>\n<p>There are two main ways to make forecasts with dynamic factor models:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Direct forecasts, where data at <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">t + h</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69841em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span></span></span></span></span> is projected on the factors at time <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.61508em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span></span></span></span></span></li>\n<li>Recursive forecasts, wehre data at <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">t + h</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69841em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span></span></span></span></span> is computed using data at time <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">t + h - 1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69841em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.77777em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></span> and so on</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The first case it suffices to have an estimate of the factors, so usually PCA is used. </p>\n<p>The second requires the dynamics to be specified, so usually a state space approach is used instead.</p>\n<h2 id=\"missing-data\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#missing-data\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Missing Data</h2>\n<p>Unfortunately in applied work missing data is quite common, and there are in general two ways to deal with this in the factor literature.</p>\n<h3 id=\"omitted-variables-are-uncorrelated-with-factors\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#omitted-variables-are-uncorrelated-with-factors\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Omitted variables are uncorrelated with factors</h3>\n<p>This is the simpler, though unrealistic case. By definition, omitted variables are idiosyncratic in this case.</p>\n<h3 id=\"omitted-variables-are-correlated-with-factors\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#omitted-variables-are-correlated-with-factors\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Omitted variables are correlated with factors</h3>\n<p>The predictor is </p>\n<h2 id=\"pca-regression-approach\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#pca-regression-approach\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>PCA Regression Approach</h2>\n<h2 id=\"genrealized-and-dynamic-pca-regression-approach\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#genrealized-and-dynamic-pca-regression-approach\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Genrealized and Dynamic PCA Regression Approach</h2>\n<h2 id=\"state-space-approach\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#state-space-approach\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>State Space Approach</h2>\n<h2 id=\"mixed-frequencies-nowcaastingbackcasting\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#mixed-frequencies-nowcaastingbackcasting\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Mixed Frequencies (Nowcaasting/Backcasting)</h2>","noteIndex":{"id":"PhD","title":"PhD Homepage","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"roadmap","alias":"roadmap","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":451},"end":{"line":12,"column":12,"offset":462},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"roadmap"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Meeting","alias":"Meeting","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":464},"end":{"line":14,"column":12,"offset":475},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"Meeting"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"TODO","alias":"TODO","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":477},"end":{"line":16,"column":9,"offset":485},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"TODO"}}],"anchors":{"quick-links":{"type":"header","text":"Quick Links","value":"quick-links","line":17,"column":0},"to-do-list":{"type":"header","text":"To do List","value":"to-do-list","line":25,"column":0}},"fname":"root","updated":1636511545745,"created":1595961348801,"parent":null,"children":["jMIh51K0sWXZgTJg24c1e","CQTUwoXQNcd0Y7la7IaAn","AiXOWFsdvi3BPZxcUMjIi","MsmFdXyWfizd5g8GGcObD","MXHvc8bQbNRRVCB0UogRy","T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","jtZSk246bVVDfJy6cdpS1","qGmGYptDKW2WLwlsu2xJw","GvwoAWaYZxq1czYi3t3k4","ZIDZSAYP9a9L7jYhVMgcz","WOnXV41UlGcOQzEoTZzJU","fhf7Gdr3mhOUG1mU5twC6","AOvKFmg0tBcGmUASXaALX","qDVp6IFHf6FiUdSgxwZMA","fHzGITjWkNNkiwsQpdex4","umGHrdI4OaLoU8OOAOdkL","aQw5xJBpqunSJYCfXXAls","0R61RLuT7e3hswR2v6o0w","AuDqSlWn0PlsSo8JdLgrR","ElqQePaEuSSz7pSeO1gNc","BMClpTRP3V8ITqM7R4kh0","SKUZ6b0dCeZkJQWeJkLAZ","y0rpX1u3Lz3vpUFro9TcW"],"body":"\nWelcome to my website!\n\nThis website has been built using Dendron, and each topic has been collated into collapsible sections on the left hand side. Below is a high level overview showing how each section is connected for ease of navigation.\n\n\n\nDendron has incredibly powerful search functionality due to good indexing, even outside of working in raw .md files. Simply use the search bar at the top of the website to find something.\n\n## Quick Links\n\n[[roadmap]]\n\n[[Meeting]]\n\n[[TODO]]\n\n## To do List\n\nType up Bai and Ng assumptions\n\nInvestigate Bates et al Assumptions\n\nInvestigate consistency of using an estimated break point in conjunction with BNIC\nThis seems to be consistent using k_tilde that itself may be Op(1)\n\nFix up BP test for better interface (low priority)\n\nImplement simulated Andrews exp and mean Wald/LM tests\n\n- look into RSpectra package (supposedly faster eigen)\n- not sure whether to rename this to SFM or not (lots of legacy code that needs to be changed)\n\nData\nFix and clean data for \n- AUMD (on hold, need to find date index)\n- FREDQD\n- CANMD (should be straightforward)\n- CANQD\n- UKMD (should be straightforward)\n\nInvestigate further sources of time series that could be used during COVID\n\nImplement truly dynamic factor models (Forni) using Dynamic PCA\n- BIG task\n- read into dynamic PCA\n- read into testing no. of dynamic factors\n- do not believe there is a literature focusing on breaks in the dynamic setup\n- implement dynamic PCA\n- implement testing no of factors, (look into ICshocks functions and make this interface better)\n- implement testing no of factors using AW test\n\nImplement BKW standard test (non sequential)\n\nFix up BKW test\n- implement a general plot method which plots *something* on the y axis, but most importantly, date on the x axis with estimated break dates, and each partition labelled with the no. of factors as determined by some consistent estimator\n\nFix up BE test\n- so that there is a consistent interface for accessing this\n\n\n\n","data":{},"contentHash":"c6af9b2ed3aab77c392e8be93bbd7ee8","custom":{"stub":false,"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"}},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":3,"useFMTitle":false,"useNoteTitleForLink":true,"noLegacyNoteRef":true,"mermaid":true,"useKatex":true,"usePrettyRefs":true,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"site":{"copyAssets":true,"siteHierarchies":["root"],"siteRootDir":"docs","usePrettyRefs":true,"title":"Ze Yu","description":"Personal knowledge space","siteLastModified":true,"gh_edit_branch":"main","duplicateNoteBehavior":{"action":"useVault","payload":["vault"]},"siteUrl":"https://zeyuz35.github.io/","usePrettyLinks":true,"siteNotesDir":"notes","siteFaviconPath":"favicon.ico","gh_edit_link":true,"gh_edit_link_text":"Edit this page on GitHub","gh_root":"docs/","gh_edit_view_mode":"edit","writeStubs":true,"siteIndex":"root"},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":false,"leaveTra